    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim (netrw I believe) can no longer open a tar.gz file via http anymore in version 0.12. This is long supported vim functionality that works on 0.11.7 and prior.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:e https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/download/nightly/nvim-macos-x86_64.tar.gz\nObserve binary garbage instead of the tar.gz file listing. The same can be observed using gf on a similar link.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOpening the tar.gz through http should open the file using the tar plugin like a local tar.gz (which still works btw).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nThe vim versions I have behave as expected.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.3.1 and Linux 5.10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezterm latest\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew (mac) and nix (linux)",
