            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "My first guess would be that netrw supplies a `BufReadCmd` for archive files, but `vim.net.request` just dumps the content into the buffer using `nvim_buf_set_lines`. So we have to set the buffers content in a way that also fires (other) `*ReadCmd`s",
            "created_at": "2026-04-03T08:02:39Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38725#issuecomment-4182421657",
