        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I took a look at the original `netrw#NetRead` implementation and it looks like this is a regression from how HTTP reads used to work.\nBefore, `netrw` would:\n1. download the remote file to a tmp file\n2. dispatch based on the original filename\n3. if file was an archive type, explcilty call tar#borws(), zip#browse etc\n\nWith `vim.net.request()` we do:\n1. fetch response boy\n2. write it directly into the buffer (we use `nvim_buf_set_lines()`)",
            "created_at": "2026-04-03T20:02:16Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38725#issuecomment-4184998371",
